               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18380820-name-341" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18380820-name-341" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18380820-name-341" type="surname" value="NUNN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18380820-name-341" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>ROBERT NUNN</persName>
                  </hi>. I am in the service of Peter Shoppee, a linen-draper, Judd-street. On the 20th of July, between twelve and one o'clock, I the prisoner take this printed cotton from the box on the step of the or—she put it under her shawl and walked away—I followed and took about four yards off—I asked her what she was going to do with it—fell on her knees and begged pardon—this is it—(<hi rend="italic">looking at it</hi>.)</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner</hi>. I was passing the window, and took up one end of the print, looked at it—he came out, and took me—he took it off the box himself. <hi rend="italic">Witness</hi>. She was walking away with it, and had just passed the window going from the house.</p>
               <p>(The prisoner received a good character.)</p>
